{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bullock_ver01/data/sn82016181/00516999627/1938021801/1378.xml":{"full_text":"U. S. Planes Reach Goal on Schedule\n(Story on Page 2)\nYesterday\nHigh\n43\nLast Night\nLow\n40\nToday\n9:30 a. m. .56\n10:30 a. m.59\n67\nNoon\n1:00 p. m. .69\nThe\nWAR\n(4\n485\n\nO)/ADSL\news\nServed by Four Trunk Wires of United Press Associations\nForecast\nCloudy and\nwarmer tonight\nwith low about\n56 degrees. To\nmorrow. occa\nsional rain;\ncolder at night.\nDr tails on\nPage 32\n17th Year\n\u2014No. 89\n3 Cents\nWASHINGTON, D. C., FRIDAY, FEBRUARY 18, 1938\nEntered\nas\nSecond\nClass\nMauer at D. C. Post Office\nHOME\nEDITION\n36\nGIRL ATHLETE FREE\nIN DEATH OF CHILD\nBalance of Prices\nIs Goal, Says F. D.\nBy United Press\nPresident Roosevelt today outlined the goal of his!\nAdministration as a balance of prices designed to end;\nbusiness recession and restore national prosperity. j\nPrice rises are sought, he said, but they should be\n(Continued on Page 6) 1\nKeep Your Feet\non the Floor\nIt seems like such a sim\nple thing to hail a cab, get\nin, roll and get out, but\nour Mr. Phillips has\nlearned from the men be\nhind the wheel that pas\nsengers can make a mess\nof mistakes. Learn \u201cHow\nto Ride a Taxi.\u201d See\nPage 12.\n7 PHILADELPHIA, Feb. 18\u2014Mary Keenan O\u2019Connor,\n19-year-old physical education student, was acquitted to\nday of killing Nancy Glenn, her 5-year-old neighbor.\nThe jury filed into the crowded court room shortly\nafter noon and was asked whether it had reached a\nverdict on two indictments, one charging murder, the\nother manslaughter.\n\u201cWe have,\u201d said Foreman Di Gilda.\n\u201cHow say you, guilty or not guilty?\u201d asked the court\nclerk.\n\u201cNot guilty on both counts,\u201d Di Gilda said in a loud\nvoice.\n(Continued on Page 6)\n\u2018Before I Die\n9\nSeven-year-old Marylyn Johns of\nKnoxville, la., seriously ill, wanted\nto see her father again \u201cbefore I\ndie.\u201d Physicians who said that\nworry over her father\u2019s absence\nfrom home has made her ill, moved\nGov. Nelson G. Kraschel to grant\nclemency to William Johns, serving\na 10-year sentence for embezzle\nment in Ft. Madison state prison.\nFather and daughter wept at their\nreunion.\nGas Perils Town Where 30 Died in Gale\n(Story on Page 2)","height":"21244","width":"14448"}}
